      "text": "Done the sweep. Here's what I found and what each chunk is actually saying.\n\n## Where \"SeedLegals\" appears in that folder\n\nOnly **5 files** contain the word. **No PDF** mentions it (scanned all 52 PDFs with pypdf). The references are all in your chat pastes / a JSON log.\n\n| # | File | Context |\n|---|---|---|\n| 1 | `Paste April 02, 2026 - 9_27PM.txt` | Sharon Kostini visa + Scrollytelling Wales equity deal |\n| 2 | `Paste April 03, 2026 - 3_10PM.txt` | Plamedi / AFJ Cardiff full governance buildout |\n| 3 | `Paste May 31, 2026 - 2_05PM.txt` | WhatsApp with Hope — Advisory Agreement |\n| 4 | `Paste May 31, 2026 - 2_08PM.txt` | **Duplicate** of #3 (same chat, re-pasted) |\n| 5 | `Validating_ADR_framework_empirically_and_factually.json` | FirstGens sweat equity math + Black Flamingo summary |\n\n## The cross-reference story (this is what connects them)\n\nSeedLegals is your **template-and-document-engine** across at least **four different people/ventures** you're advising. It's not just one project — it's the same platform being reused as your \"legal scaffolding\" tool everywhere:\n\n### 1. FirstGens / Alaya (the .json, lines 1117 / 3009 / 3715 / 3740)\n- Cites SeedLegals + Vestd as the UK benchmark for non-technical-founder vs incoming-tech-cofounder equity splits.\n- Builds out the **15% sweat-equity model** for you entering FirstGens: 1-year cliff, 4-year vesting, 0.3125%/month, double-trigger acceleration.\n- Talks about how signing a **SeedLegals cap-table/equity agreement** will sweep your existing ADRs into the company via the standard IP-assignment clause.\n- Also flags Black Flamingo Beauty (Mariam) — you raised SeedLegals **share-options** as an item with her earlier.\n\n### 2. AFJ Cardiff / Plamedi (April 3 paste — long one)\nThis is the most extensive use. SeedLegals gets pulled in for almost every governance document:\n- **IP Assignment** — moving Plamedi's manual handbook, logo, curriculum from her UTR → AFJ Cardiff Ltd\n- **Founders Service Agreement** — formalising you as Digital Officer under the Ltd\n- **Consultancy Agreement** (with SLA appendix) — to legally air-gap your personal liability\n- **Sonia's contract** (the marketer she wants to hire) — Stiwdio £1k startup fund earmarked to pay for it\n- **Data Room** — SeedLegals receives a webhook per \"Governance Event\" so the immutable vault = their data room\n- **Equity Option Letter** for board members / mentors, framed as the institutional passport\n- Cost line item: **£30/month** Standard plan, sitting in a £31/mo total burn stack\n- Also referenced alongside DocuSign/Dropbox Sign as the \"Legal Tech\" peer benchmark for version-level immutability (SEC Rule 17a-4 / MiFID II / eIDAS framing)\n\n### 3. Sharon / Scrollytelling Wales (April 2, 9:27PM paste)\nSeedLegals is the **frame** for her Spousal Visa evidence pack:\n- \"Legal Pack\" modeled on SeedLegals standards: NDA + Consultancy Agreement + IP Waiver\n- **Advisory Agreement / Consultancy for Equity (C4E)** — formalising the £860 retainer + 2% equity\n- **Letter of Intent for Equity Grant** — pre-incorporation conditional equity offer (with 12-month vesting)\n- Common Paper flagged as the **free alternative** to SeedLegals for the actual template text\n- PandaDoc/Dropbox Sign do the signature ceremony; SeedLegals vocabulary is what makes it read \"professional\" to the Home Office auditor\n\n### 4. Hope / charity (May 31 pastes — duplicates)\nJust one line from you: *\"I am preparing a founder doc from SeedLegals… Advisory Agreement. They also have a founder's one I can pass on to you.\"* No follow-up content. Both files are the same WhatsApp export pasted twice.\n\n## What SeedLegals actually *is* in your workflow\n\nIt's your **default UK legal-document generator** for:\n- Founders Service Agreements\n- Advisor / Consultancy-for-Equity (C4E) agreements\n- Sweat equity + vesting math\n- IP Assignment\n- Letters of Intent for Equity Grants\n- Cap table management\n- Data Room hosting\n\nYou pair it with **Common Paper** (when you want free OSS templates), **PandaDoc/Dropbox Sign** (for signatures), **Oracle Cloud** (for the immutable vault that backs it), and **Authentik SSO** (for the access layer). SeedLegals is the legal-language layer; everything else is plumbing around it.\n\nIf you want, I can also pull out the **specific clauses** drafted in any of those pastes (e.g. Sharon's LOI, the 15% vesting model, the IP assignment wording for Plamedi) into clean standalone docs so they're actually usable instead of buried in chat logs. Just say the word.",
