      "text": "The python output didn't give any hits (no `### filename ###` printed). Good - confirms no PDF mentions SeedLegals.\n\nLet me also quickly check whether the file \"LAMPForge PDE\" or other workspace folders contain seedlegals content — actually no, the user explicitly asked about the Google AI Studio folder. I've completed the cross-reference.\n\nNow let me give the user a clean, useful summary of:\n1. All 5 files that mention SeedLegals\n2. What each one says about SeedLegals in context\n3. The cross-reference narrative\n\nThe key narrative across all 5 files is that SeedLegals is being used as the **reference standard / template provider** for UK startup legal documents (Founders Service Agreement, Advisor Agreement, Consultancy Agreement, IP Assignment, Letter of Intent for Equity Grant, Sweat Equity math, Cap Table). It's not just one project — it's woven across multiple ventures Andie is advising/working with:\n\n1. **FirstGens (Alaya Holloway)** — Sweat equity math, 15% allocation, vesting, cap table, SEIS. References in Validating_ADR json file.\n2. **AFJ Cardiff (Plamedi)** — Full governance architecture using SeedLegals templates: IP Assignment, Founders Service Agreement, Consultancy Agreement, Sonia's contract, Equity Option Letter, Data Room. References across April 2 (Sovereign 2026) and April 3 pastes.\n3. **Black Flamingo Beauty (Mariam)** — SeedLegals share options flagging. Mentioned in the Validating_ADR json conversation summary.\n4. **Sharon Kostini (Scrollytelling Wales / RAEng)** — Advisor Agreement, Letter of Intent for Equity Grant, Vesting Schedule, equity kicker. References in April 2 paste (the 9:27PM file).\n5. **Hope** (charity WhatsApp chat, May 31) — Andie preparing a founder doc from SeedLegals as \"Advisory Agreement\". References in May 31 2:05PM and 2:08PM pastes (which are identical content).\n\nThe two May 31 pastes appear to be WhatsApp chat exports that contain the same message thread. They look like duplicates.\