      "type": "thought",
      "text": "OK so I've now confirmed:\n- SeedLegals Data Room is **included free** in all memberships (no extra cost)\n- SeedLegals pricing: Access £649/year, Funding £1,199/year (with Boost), Options £2,699/year\n- SeedLegals has no public webhook/API docs (developers.seedlegals.com doesn't exist)\n- Common Paper is **FREE** under CC BY 4.0 (they even have an API: api.commonpaper.com)\n- Data Room FAQ mentions it's \"no extra charge for SeedLegals members\"\n\nSo the chat paste's mention of \"SeedLegals is notified via webhook that a new 'Governance Event' has been vaulted\" — that's **fictional/aspirational**. SeedLegals does NOT have a public webhook API. The data room is a UI-only feature (upload, share via Groups, etc.). No way for an external system to programmatically push to it.\n\nLet me also check the free entry point and alternatives. Let me search for Carta UK / Vestd / Capdesk / others.",
