      "type": "thought",
      "text": "Two questions:\n1. IT Contractors Alliance — how much?\n2. How do I build Decision IDs?\n\nFor #1, let me search for current pricing. The IT Contractors Alliance is a UK organisation that offers PI insurance and other services for IT contractors. Let me check.\n\nFor #2, this is a domain concept from the chat pastes. Decision IDs are essentially unique identifiers (UUIDs) that tie a \"decision event\" (like a contract signed, a rule triggered) to a specific timestamp + actor + context. They're a common pattern in:\n- Rules engines (GoRules, Camunda, etc.)\n- Audit trails / governance systems\n- Event-sourced architectures\n\nLet me explain practically how to build one. From the April 3 paste, the Decision ID was framed as: \"every time a school signs up, the system generates a 'Decision ID.' This is a permanent legal record of exactly why we charged them that price and which policy they signed.\"\n\nPractically it requires:\n1. A UUID generator\n2. A timestamp (RFC 3339)\n3. A \"decision payload\" — the rule logic + inputs + outputs\n4. A \"subject\" — what entity the decision is about (signer, organisation, document)\n5. Storage (immutable)\n6. Hash of the signed PDF to bindit to the decision\n\nLet me search for ITCA pricing.",
