      "type": "answer",
      "text": "Here's the full picture. I'll break it down by what each place is actually good for, since \"free contract templates\" is a noisy category.\n\n## Common Paper — the full catalog (the one I flagged before)\n\n**Where it lives:** [commonpaper.com/standards](https://commonpaper.com/standards/) + [commonpaper.com/language-library](https://commonpaper.com/language-library/)\n\n**License:** CC BY 4.0 (free, just credit them)\n\n**Main agreements (the 12 \"Standard\" suite):**\n1. **Mutual NDA** — covers Sharon's visa pack, school partner onboarding, etc.\n2. **Terms of Service** — for AFJ Cardiff's portal\n3. **Design Partner Agreement** — for your first school pilot\n4. **Cloud Service Agreement** — for selling any SaaS\n5. **Service Level Agreement** — pairs with the CSA\n6. **Data Processing Agreement** — UK GDPR / EU GDPR\n7. **Business Associate Agreement** — HIPAA / NHS use cases\n8. **Professional Services Agreement** — for Sharon / Mariam consultancy work\n9. **AI Addendum** — bolt-on for any AI you build into AFJ's platform\n10. **Partnership Agreement** — for A&B Cymru, Stiwdio, etc.\n11. **Software License Agreement** — for selling on-prem or self-hosted\n12. **Pilot Agreement** — for the first school trial before full rollout\n\n**Other documents (the 7 \"Other documents\" list):**\n- Letter of Intent (LOI) — what your April 2 paste drafted for Sharon\n- One-way NDA\n- Term Sheet\n- Independent Contractor Agreement — covers Mariam, Hope, etc.\n- Amendment\n- Statement of Work (SOW)\n- Order Form — pairs with the CSA\n\n**Language Library add-ons** (this is gold): 40+ pre-written optional clauses you can paste into the Cover Page — AI training, BAA inclusion, late-payment penalty, EU Data Act rights, OSS disclaimer, logo rights, governing law, JAMS arbitration, etc. This is what makes Common Paper actually customisable without redrafting.\n\n**API access:** [api.commonpaper.com/docs](https://api.commonpaper.com/docs) — you can generate agreements programmatically (useful for n8n). They also have an AI agent for negotiation review.\n\n**Committee:** 30+ lawyers from Wilson Sonsini, Cooley, Orrick, Goodwin, Gunderson, Andreessen Horowitz legal team, Cloudflare legal, etc. Updated quarterly.\n\n---\n\n## Other free / cheap places you'll actually use\n\n### **Y Combinator — free, public, US-style but UK-adaptable**\n- **post-money SAFE** (the one Mark Suster & all the US angels use) — [ycombinator.com/documents](https://www.ycombinator.com/documents)\n- **Series AA** docs (now public — YC open-sourced them in 2024)\n- **Bridge Notes** template\n- **Accredited Investor Questionnaire**\n- **Pro Rata Side Letter**\n- **MFN Side Letter**\n- **Use:** safe notes, convertible instruments, angel/seed fundraising docs. Not Common Paper's strength.\n\n### **Cooley GO — free, law-firm-published**\n- **cooleygo.com** — Cooley's startup resource library\n- **Cooley CooleyGoDoc library** — 30+ free templates: founder agreement, IP assignment, employment offer letters, board consents, 83(b) elections, NDA, advisor agreements\n- **Quality:** top-tier (Cooley is the leading tech law firm)\n- **Caveat:** US-style, but most are easy to UK-adapt for equity grants\n- **Use:** the 83(b) election template, board consent templates, advisor agreements\n\n### **Goodwin Procter — free**\n- **Procter & Gamble startup docs** — they published a similar library\n- **Goodwin's \"ProNoFA\"** — public forms library for emerging companies\n- **Use:** alternative to Cooley GO; often has UK/EU variants\n\n### **Wilson Sonsini — free for some, paid for others**\n- **WSGR Term Sheet Generator** — they've open-sourced their standard Series A/seed term sheet generator\n- **WSGR Document Library** — limited but high quality\n\n### **Andreessen Horowitz (a16z) — free**\n- **a16z \"Startup Docs\"** — they open-sourced their standard founder/equity docs\n- **Use:** modern US-style founder agreement, IP assignment, advisor docs. Free.\n\n### **Orrick — free**\n- **Orrick \"Doc Generator\"** — they have a public startup documents library\n- **Use:** NVCA-based docs (heavily US) but the NDA and advisor agreement templates are solid\n\n### **Clerky / Stripe / Mercury — free templates**\n- **Clerky** — premium (~$500/one-time) but has excellent templates; **their free blog posts** walk through the legal reasoning behind every clause\n- **Stripe Atlas** — paid ($500) but includes standard US LLC/C-corp docs\n- **Mercury** — no docs but their blog has \"legal guides for startups\"\n\n### **GitHub repos (open-source contracts)**\n- **github.com/openlegalstandard** — community-maintained open contracts\n- **github.com/standard-law** — proposed OpenLaw standard\n- **github.com/awesome-legal** — curated list of legal resources\n- **github.com/a16z/open-source-legal-templates** — a16z's published templates\n\n### **EU / EEA public sector**\n- **EU Model Contracts** — for EU-funded projects (Horizon Europe, ERC grants)\n- **EUPL (European Union Public License)** — for OSS you contribute to\n- **DIGITAL Europe Programme** — model grant agreements\n\n### **UK Government — free**\n- **GOV.UK contract templates** — [gov.uk/guidance/contracts-and-rights-for-self-employed](https://www.gov.uk/guidance/contracts-and-rights-for-self-employed) — basic UK self-employment contract\n- **Companies House** — standard Model Articles for Ltd companies (you adopt these or customise)\n- **ICO (Information Commissioner's Office)** — UK GDPR guidance + template DPA clauses for controllers/processors\n- **HMRC** — IR35 / off-payroll templates\n- **Crown Commercial Service** — public sector contract templates\n- **Welsh Government** — supplier contract templates (relevant if Stiwdio grants have procurement requirements)\n\n### **UK-specific open-source**\n- **OpenSAFELY** — published governance templates (for health-data programmes, NHS-style)\n- **Open Data Institute (ODI)** — data sharing agreement templates\n- **ICO Accountability Framework** — template clauses for UK GDPR compliance\n\n### **Privacy / DPA generators (free tier + paid)**\n- **iubenda** — generator, freemium\n- **TermsFeed** — generator, freemium\n- **GetTerms.io** — generator\n- **FreePrivacyPolicy.com** — basic generator\n\n### **Open-source licences (different category, but useful for IP)**\n- **MIT, BSD, Apache 2.0, MPL 2.0** — opensource.org\n- **AGPL, LGPL, GPL** — gnu.org\n- **EUPL** — joinup.ec.europa.eu\n- **CC0, CC BY, CC BY-SA, CC BY-NC** — creativecommons.org\n\n---\n\n## How to combine these for your specific plays\n\nHere's what I'd actually use, case by case:\n\n| Venture / need | Use this | Where |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Sharon's visa pack** | Common Paper NDA + Common Paper Independent Contractor Agreement + Common Paper LOI | commonpaper.com |\n| **Plamedi's consultancy pack** | Common Paper PSA + Common Paper DPA + Common Paper AI Addendum + Common Paper Amendment (for SLA appendix) | commonpaper.com |\n| **Plamedi's portal ToS / Privacy** | Common Paper Terms of Service + Common Paper DPA | commonpaper.com |\n| **FirstGens / Alaya equity** | SeedLegals cap-table + sweat equity maths (paid); or free DIY with YC SAFE + Common Paper LOI | seedlegals.com / ycombinator.com/documents / commonpaper.com |\n| **AFJ Cardiff seed raise (when ready)** | YC post-money SAFE (free) + Common Paper Term Sheet | ycombinator.com / commonpaper.com |\n| **Black Flamingo share options** | Vestd (paid, cheaper than SeedLegals for EMI) | vestd.com |\n| **Hope's charity MOU** | Common Paper Letter of Intent + your own short advisory addendum | commonpaper.com |\n| **IP assignment (any venture)** | Common Paper PSA Section 2 (Feedback Assignment add-on) + a SeedLegals-style IP Assignment if equity is involved | commonpaper.com / seedlegals.com |\n| **UK GDPR / ICO compliance** | Common Paper DPA + ICO controller-processor guidance + your own ROPA | commonpaper.com / ico.org.uk |\n| **AFJ Cardiff + Schools partnership** | Common Paper Partnership Agreement + Common Paper Design Partner Agreement + Common Paper Pilot Agreement | commonpaper.com |\n| **Your own Ltd's standard terms** | Common Paper Cloud Service Agreement (adapted for your consultancy) + Common Paper ToS for any client portal | commonpaper.com |\n| **Open-source contributions from your Ltd** | Apache 2.0 or MIT (chooseapache.org / choosealicense.com) | opensource.org |\n\n---\n\n## My one-line recommendation\n\n**Use Common Paper as your default for 80% of what you need.** It's the only free library that's written by actual BigLaw lawyers and structured so both sides can negotiate quickly. Pull YC SAFE + Cooley advisor template for the equity side. Pull ICO clauses for UK GDPR. Pull Welsh Government templates if Stiwdio grants ask for procurement-style docs. Everything else is paid (SeedLegals/Vestd) or low-quality.\n\nWant me to draft the actual **Cover Pages** (the variable parts) for each of the ventures — Alaya, Plamedi, Sharon, Mariam, Hope — so you've got Common Paper agreements ready to populate in one sitting?",
      "timestamp": 1782215448102
    },
