      "text": "Got the full Common Paper catalog. Now let me give the user a comprehensive list of all the places they can find these standard contract templates — Common Paper + the alternatives I know about. Let me think about what else exists in the public domain:\n\nFree / OSS contract template libraries:\n1. **Common Paper** — what we discussed\n2. **Creative Commons** itself — open licenses for sharing\n3. **GitHub** — open-source repos of legal templates (awesome-legal, Y Combinator rfs templates)\n4. **OpenLaw** by Morrison Foerster — discontinued but archived\n5. **Hack.lu / EFF** — privacy/security focused templates\n6. **Electronic Frontier Foundation** — surveillance self-defense, but also has license/contract templates\n7. **Mozilla** — MPL and various open-source license templates\n8. **Creative Commons** — CC0, CC BY, etc.\n9. **Open Source Initiative** — license templates\n10. **Open Data Commons** — license templates\n11. **FSF** — GPL, AGPL, LGPL\n12. **Terms of Service; Didn't Read** — meta-rating\n13. **iubenda** — generator\n14. **TermsFeed** — generator\n15. **GetTerms.io** — generator\n\nBigLaw / corporate:\n1. **Wilson Sonsini** — has published some pro bono templates\n2. **Cooley** — GO venture program templates (free for portfolio companies)\n3. **Orrick** — has some open templates\n4. **WSGR** — has published templates via their startup resource\n5. **Goodwin Procter** — free templates for startups\n6. **Cooley GO** — great free resource\n7. **Y Combinator's SAFE** — now public\n8. **Y Combinator's Series AA docs** — now public  \n9. **Y Combinator's post-money SAFE** — also public\n\nOpen-source / community:\n1. **awesome-legal** GitHub repo\n2. **Open Source Contracts** by various\n3. **EUPL** — European Union Public License\n4. **AGPL** — Affero GPL\n\nUK-specific:\n1. **ICO** (Information Commissioner's Office) — UK GDPR guidance and template clauses\n2. **ICO contracts** for data processing\n3. **Companies House** — standard articles of association\n4. **ICAEW** — accounting templates\n5. **Law Society** — precedent library (paid)\n6. **STEP** — trust templates\n7. **HMRC** — various template agreements\n8. **GOV.UK** — public sector contract templates\n\nUK startup ecosystem:\n1. **SeedLegals** (paid)\n2. **Vestd** (paid)\n3. **Capdesk** (paid)\n4. **Juno** (formerly LegalEdge) (paid)\n5. **Founders Factory** resources\n6. **Tech Nation** (now defunct but archived)\n7. **Techstars** accelerator templates\n\nGovernment and public sector:\n1. **GOV.UK** — public sector contracts\n2. **Crown Commercial Service** — government contract templates\n3. **EU public sector** — model contracts\n\nInternational:\n1. **UNIDROIT** — model contracts\n2. **ICC** — model contracts\n\nLet me also think about the more specific templates that match what the user needs:\n- For Sharon's visa pack: NDA, Consultancy Agreement (independent contractor), IP Waiver/Assignment\n- For Plamedi: Founders Service Agreement, IP Assignment, Consultancy + SLA\n- For Hope: Advisory Agreement, simple MOU\n\nSo the key templates they need:\n- **NDA / Mutual NDA** — Common Paper has this free\n- **Independent Contractor / Consultancy Agreement** — Common Paper has this; also Cooley GO\n- **PSA (Professional Services Agreement)** — Common Paper\n- **CSA (Cloud Service Agreement)** — Common Paper\n- **DPA (Data Processing Agreement)** — Common Paper\n- **ToS (Terms of Service)** — Common Paper\n- **SLA (Service Level Agreement)** — Common Paper\n- **IP Assignment** — Common Paper has it as an add-on; also SeedLegals has it built-in\n- **Advisory Agreement** — Common Paper has it via Independent Contractor + LOI\n- **Founders Agreement** — Common Paper doesn't have one specifically; YC has published SAFEs and Series docs; SeedLegals/Vestd are paid\n- **SAFE / Post-Money SAFE** — Y Combinator publishes these free\n- **Term Sheet** — Common Paper has it as a doc\n- **LOI** — Common Paper has it as a doc\n- **BAA (Business Associate Agreement)** — Common Paper (HIPAA)\n\nLet me give the user a comprehensive list organized bywhat they need.",
