      "text": "The user is asking two things:\n\n1. **\"but it says .com so its not proper complete is it? the first one u showed me.\"** — They're asking about Common Paper. They saw `commonpaper.com` and are concerned it's not \"complete\" or \"proper\" because of the `.com` TLD. They want to know if Common Paper is the full real deal or just a `.com` placeholder. I should clarify: Common Paper Inc. is a real Delaware-incorporated company, founded by Adam P. Klivans (formerly of Dropbox legal), backed by Index Ventures, with an actual product (Common Paper app + standard contracts), 40,000+ downloads, 60+ top-tier lawyers on the committee. The `.com` is just the domain — it has nothing to do with completeness or credibility.\n\n2. **\"and also these ones where u said: Pull Welsh Government templates if Stiwdio grants ask for procurement-style docs.\"** — They want me to actually find and link the Welsh Government procurement/contract templates.\n\nLet me search for theactual Welsh Government supplier contract templates, and also verify Common Paper's credentials.",
