      "output": "              Start up and business planning | Business Wales                        \n\n[Skip to main content](#main-content)\n\nWe use JavaScript to set most of our cookies. Unfortunately JavaScript is not running on your browser, so you cannot change your settings using this page. To control your cookie settings using this page try turning on JavaScript in your browser.\n\n[About cookies](https://businesswales.gov.wales/cookie-settings)\n\nWe've saved some files called cookies on your device. These cookies are:\n\n-   essential for the site work\n-   to help improve our website by collecting and reporting information on how you use it\n\nWe would also like to save some cookies to help:\n\n-   improve our website by measuring website usage\n-   remember your settings\n\nAccept cookies [Change cookie settings](https://businesswales.gov.wales/cookie-settings)\n\nYou've accepted all cookies for this website. You can [change your cookie preferences](/cookie-settings) at any time.\n\nHide\n\n[![Llywodraeth Cymru | Welsh Government](/themes/contrib/gel2/img/logos/wg-logo.svg)](https://gov.wales)\n\n-   [English](/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning)\n-   [Cymraeg](https://busnescymru.llyw.cymru/pynciau-a-chyfarwyddyd/dechrau-busnes/dechrau-a-chynllunio-busnes)\n\n \n\nSearch term  Search Business Wales website\n\n[![Busnes Cymru | Business Wales](/themes/custom/main_gel2/img/logos/logo.svg?v2)](https://businesswales.gov.wales/)\n\nMenu\n\n-   [Home](/ \"Home\")\n-   [News and blog](/news-and-blog)\n-   [Topics and guidance](/topics-and-guidance)\n-   [Specialist services](/specialist-services)\n-   [Success stories](/success-stories)\n\n1.  [Home](/)\n2.  [Topics and guidance](/topics-and-guidance)\n3.  [Starting a business](/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business)\n4.  Start up and business planning\n\nSub-topic\n\n# Start up and business planning\n\n## Self employment\n\n[Is self-employment for you?](/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning/self-employment-you)\n\nStarting a business of your own is a huge and exciting challenge. This guide outlines some of the key things you should consider before you take that big step.\n\n[Developing your business idea](/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning/developing-your-business-idea)\n\nBefore you start your business, you need to decide what sort of business it is going to be.\n\n[Research and develop your business ideas, new products and services](/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning/research-and-develop-your-business-ideas-new-products-and-services)\n\nDeveloping your business idea into a viable product or service is a critical part of building a business\n\n[Getting help](/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning/getting-help)\n\nOne of the toughest things about running your own business is feeling that you have to do it all on your own and wondering how you are going to fund it. Rest assured, no-one expects you to know everything and there’s plenty of support out there.\n\n[It's the law!](/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning/its-law)\n\nAlthough starting your business is an exciting prospect, there are a number of tax and legal issues that you have to consider.\n\n[Common mistakes when starting up - and how to avoid them](/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning/common-mistakes-when-starting-and-how-avoid-them)\n\nLaunching a small business can be risky and success is not always guaranteed\n\n## Business plan\n\n[Making a plan](/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning/making-a-plan)\n\nPlanning what you want to do in your business is an important part of making your business a success.\n\n## Market research\n\n[What is Market Research?](/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning/what-market-research)\n\nIt’s easy to believe you have an excellent idea for a business, however, if your business is to be a success, you need to confirm and verify that belief.\n\n[Understanding Your Market](/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning/understanding-your-market)\n\nThe world is moving fast and it’s important to identify the trends in your market, locally, nationally and globally.\n\n[Checking out the competition](/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning/checking-out-competition)\n\nEveryone has competitors and it’s important to know who they are and what they offer.\n\n[Identifying your customer](/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning/identifying-your-customer)\n\nKnowing who is likely to buy your product or service is fundamental to your business.\n\n[Types of Market Research](/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning/types-market-research)\n\nMarket research is about gathering information to help you make better decisions.\n\n[Planning and using your market research](/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning/planning-and-using-your-market-research)\n\nMarket research is about gathering information so that you are better informed and can make better decisions about your business.\n\n## Marketing\n\n[What is Marketing?](/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning/what-marketing)\n\nMarketing is about making sure the right people know about what you have to offer, getting them to come to you and getting them to buy.\n\n[What are you selling?](/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning/what-are-you-selling)\n\nWhilst the answer to this question may seem obvious, your approach to it can be the difference between success and failure.\n\n[Know your Customer](/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning/know-your-customer)\n\nForget trying to sell to everyone. Instead you want to sell to people who you know will want your product or servic\n\n[Right Place, Right Time](/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning/right-place-right-time)\n\nIt is important to make sure your product or service is available in the right place at the right time and in the right quality.\n\n[Promoting your business](/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning/promoting-your-business)\n\nGetting your message in front of potential customers and persuading them to buy is a challenge.\n\n[Practical marketing planning](/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning/practical-marketing-planning)\n\nBefore you jump into “doing” marketing or spending any money on marketing, it’s essential to pull everything together in a Marketing Action Plan.\n\n[Selling for success](/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning/selling-success)\n\nMarketing is all about finding the right customer for your products and services and getting them to come to you.\n\n[Getting your first customer](/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning/getting-your-first-customer)\n\nThe very first customer is always the hardest to land.\n\n## Finance\n\n[Costs, Price and Value](/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning/costs-price-and-value)\n\nSetting prices is challenging. The amount of profit you make depends to a great extent on the prices you charge, so getting the price right is vital to your business success.\n\n[Personal Survival Budget](/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning/personal-survival-budget)\n\nIn order for your business to survive, you need to have enough money to cover all your start-up costs, the costs of running the business and also for you to live on.\n\n[Understanding Costs](/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning/understanding-costs)\n\nThe first step in setting prices it to establish your costs.\n\n[Costing your product or service](/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning/costing-your-product-or-service)\n\nNow that you’ve identified what it costs to start and run your business, you can work out the cost of producing your product or providing your service.\n\n[Pricing](/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning/pricing)\n\nPricing is a complex area. Set your prices too high and you may lose the sale.\n\n[How do I survive until my business is off the ground?](/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning/how-do-i-survive-until-my-business-ground)\n\nIt can be a number of months before a new business is profitable and generating a cash surplus.\n\n[Business Finance (Finding Finance)](/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning/business-finance-finding-finance)\n\nFunding, grants, finance\n\n## Managing your finances\n\n[Understanding the basics](/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning/understanding-basics)\n\nA vital part of running a successful business is looking after your finances. When they’re put together in the right way, the numbers paint a detailed picture and tell stories about your business.\n\n[Cashflow forecast](/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning/cashflow-forecast)\n\nYour cashflow shows the amount of cash coming in and going out of the business each month\n\n[Profit and Loss Account](/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning/profit-and-loss-account)\n\nA Profit and Loss Account shows the financial performance of your business over a specific period.\n\n[Forecasting Sales](/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning/forecasting-sales)\n\nForecasting sales is an important part of business planning.\n\n[Balance Sheet and ratios](/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning/balance-sheet-and-ratios)\n\nA Balance Sheet gives you a snapshot of the financial state of your business at a given point in time. It is used to assess the value of your business and to work out the ratios which evaluate business performance. This section gives you an overview of the Balance Sheet and also explains the most\n\n[Value Added Tax (VAT)](/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning/value-added-tax-vat)\n\nValue Added Tax (VAT) is a transaction tax charged on the sale of goods and services\n\n[Managing finance effectively](/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning/managing-finance-effectively)\n\nThe importance of good financial management is emphasised throughout this module.\n\n[Keeping track of your finances](/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning/keeping-track-your-finances)\n\nA vital part of running a successful business is looking after your finances. When they’re put together in the right way,\n\n## Building a team\n\n[What is a Limited Company](/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning/what-a-limited-company)\n\nWhen you start a business, you need to choose the legal status of your business, You have to decide if you are going to run it as a Sole Trader, a Partnership, or a Limited Company.\n\n[Directors’ duties and responsibilities](/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning/directors-duties-and-responsibilities)\n\nTaking on a directorship is a serious undertaking. It can be a fulfilling and prestigious role.\n\n[The director’s role](/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning/directors-role)\n\nAs has already been explained, the directors run a limited company and the shareholders (members) own and fund it\n\n[Corporate Governance](/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning/corporate-governance)\n\nCorporate governance is the system by which companies are directed and controlled.\n\n[Creating an effective board](/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning/creating-effective-board)\n\nFor many small business owners, working with a board of directors can be a new experience and can be a challenge.\n\n[Ready to recruit?](/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning/ready-recruit)\n\nTaking on your first employee is one of the most important steps in the development of your business.\n\n[Key stages of the recruitment process](/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning/key-stages-recruitment-process)\n\nSmall businesses can find the recruitment process a daunting prospect. They are concerned that it’s a complicated process, and that there are challenges at every stage.\n\n[Getting ready for your new employee](/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning/getting-ready-your-new-employee)\n\nHaving made your decision and selected your candidate, there are a number of things to consider before they become an employee.\n\n[Taking on your first employee - legal issues](/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning/taking-your-first-employee-legal-issues)\n\nWhen you take on an employee for the first time, there are a number of key things you need to do under UK law.\n\n## Further guides\n\n[The General Data Protection Regulation](/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning/general-data-protection-regulation)\n\nThis guide provides an introduction to the General Data Protection Regulation.\n\n[Buy an existing business](/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning/buy-existing-business)\n\nf you're thinking about running your own business, buying a company that's already established may be quicker and easier than starting from scratch.\n\n[Buy a franchise](/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning/buy-a-franchise)\n\nTaking on a franchise is an option worth considering for anyone who wants to run a business but doesn't have a specific business idea or prefers the security provided by an established concept.\n\n[Obtaining information on a business you are thinking of buying](/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning/obtaining-information-a-business-you-are-thinking-buying)\n\nBuying an established business is a good option for some aspiring entrepreneurs. Much of the groundwork for success may have already been done by the existing owners.\n\n[Starting a business from home](/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning/starting-a-business-home)\n\nIf you are thinking of starting your own business you should consider the possibility of working from home. Home-based businesses are a popular option for many types of smaller business. Generally the costs will be lower, you can avoid travel expenses and you have the freedom and flexibility to work\n\n[Use your home as a workplace](/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning/use-your-home-a-workplace)\n\nIf you are planning to set up and run a 'work at home' business, there are a number of points to check before you begin.\n\n[Choose the right name for your business](/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning/choose-right-name-your-business)\n\nChoosing a name for your business is a creative and enjoyable process.\n\n[Starting a part-time business](/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning/starting-a-part-time-business)\n\nStarting a business, although highly exciting, is a big step to take.\n\n[Insure your business and assets - general insurances](/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning/insure-your-business-and-assets-general-insurances)\n\nInsurance can protect your business against damage to, or the loss of, physical assets.\n\n[Outsourcing](/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning/outsourcing)\n\nOutsourcing is when you contract out a business function - a particular task, role or process - to a third party over a substantial period of time. This third-party organisation takes control of the function and becomes responsible for its success.\n\n[Collaboration](/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning/collaboration)\n\nCollaboration and working in partnership with other businesses can be one way to help your business grow.\n\n## Business Startup Factsheets\n\n[Business Startup Factsheet](/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning/business-startup-factsheet)\n\nFind a business idea\n\n---\n\n## Follow us on Business Wales\n\n-   [X](https://twitter.com/_businesswales \"Link to X\")\n-   [Facebook](https://www.facebook.com/businesswales.gov.wales \"Link to Facebook\")\n-   [LinkedIn](https://www.linkedin.com/company/business-wales-busnes-cymru \"Link to LinkedIn\")\n-   [YouTube](https://www.youtube.com/user/businesswales?feature=results_main \"Link to YouTube\")\n-   [Instagram](https://www.instagram.com/businesswales_busnescymru/ \"Link to Instagram\")\n\n[Sign up to receive email newsletters](https://public.govdelivery.com/accounts/UKWALES/subscriber/new?topic_id=UKWALES_10 \"Link to sign up to receive email newsletters\")\n\n## Business Wales Helpline\n\n03000 6 03000\n\nLines are open 10am to 4pm Monday to Friday.\n\nRydym yn croesawu galwadau'n Gymraeg.\n\n[Report anything wrong with this page](mailto:Businesssupport@gov.wales?url=https://businesswales.gov.wales/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning&subject=Report%20on%20https://businesswales.gov.wales/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning&body=Page%20URL%20https://businesswales.gov.wales/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning \"Link to report errors with page\")\n\nShare this page\n\n-   [X](https://twitter.com/share?url=https://businesswales.gov.wales/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning \"Share via X\")\n-   [Facebook](https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=https://businesswales.gov.wales/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning \"Share via Facebook\")\n-   [Email](mailto:?body=https://businesswales.gov.wales/topics-and-guidance/starting-a-business/start-and-business-planning&subject=Shared%20from%20Business%20Wales \"Share via Email\")\n\n[Back to top](#top-anchor)\n\n-   [About Business Wales](/business-wales-service \"Link to About\")\n-   [Contact us](/contact-us \"Link to Contact us\")\n\n-   [Cookies](/cookie-settings \"Link to Cookies\")\n-   [Privacy Policy](/privacy-notice-index-digital \"Link to Privacy Policy\")\n-   [Terms & Conditions](/terms-conditions \"Link to Terms & Conditions\")\n-   [Accessibility](/accessibility-statement-business-wales \"Link to Accessibility\")\n-   [Copyright](/copyright \"Link to Copyright\")\n-   [Welsh language policy](/welsh-language-policy \"Link to Welsh language policy\")\n-   [Economic Action Plan](/economic-action-plan \"Link to Economic Action Plan\")\n\n[![Welsh Government](/themes/contrib/gel2/img/logos/wg-logo--dark.svg)](https://gov.wales)\n\nAll content is available under the Open Government License, except where otherwise stated.",
