      "output": "                                     Procurement Act 2023: guidance documents | GOV.WALES   \n\n[Skip to main content](#wg_main)\n\nGOV.WALES uses cookies which are essential for the site to work. Non-essential cookies are also used to tailor and improve services. By continuing to use this site, you agree to our use of cookies.\n\n[About cookies](/help/cookies)\n\n[Home](https://www.gov.wales/ \"Welsh Government\")![Welsh Government](/themes/custom/govwales/images/print/logo.png)\n\n-   [English](/procurement-act-2023-guidance-documents)\n-   [Cymraeg](https://www.llyw.cymru/deddf-caffael-2023-dogfennau-canllaw)\n\nSearch \n\nYou are here:\n\n-   [Home](/)\n-   [Public sector (Topic)](/public-sector)\n-   [Public sector procurement (Sub-topic)](/public-sector-procurement)\n-   Procurement Act 2023: guidance documents\n\nCollection\n\n# Procurement Act 2023: guidance documents\n\nGuidance on all aspects of the Procurement Act 2023 and associated Welsh regulations. Includes technical guidance and walk-through videos.\n\nPart of:\n\n-   [Public sector procurement (Sub-topic)](/public-sector-procurement)\n\nFirst published:\n\n12 August 2024\n\nLast updated:\n\n15 August 2025\n\n## In this collection\n\n-   [Introduction](#Introduction)\n-   [Overarching guidance](#Overarchingguidance)\n-   [Plan](#Plan)\n-   [Define](#Define)\n-   [Procure](#Procure)\n-   [Manage](#Manage)\n\n## Introduction\n\nThis guidance supports preparation for the Procurement Act 2023. It covers all aspects of the new procurement regime.\n\n## Overarching guidance\n\n-   [Procurement reform in Wales](/procurement-reform-wales)\n    \n    19 August 2024 Guidance\n    \n-   [Expressions and definitions](/procurement-act-2023-guidance-expressions-and-definitions)\n    \n    11 July 2024 Guidance\n    \n-   [Welsh Digital Platform](/procurement-act-2023-welsh-digital-platform)\n    \n    12 February 2025 Guidance\n    \n-   [Notice sequencing and flowcharts](/procurement-act-2023-guidance-notice-sequencing-and-flowcharts)\n    \n    16 June 2025 Guidance\n    \n-   [Central Digital Platform](/procurement-act-2023-guidance-central-digital-platform-and-publication-of-information)\n    \n    24 February 2025 Guidance\n    \n\n## Plan\n\nHaving clear and transparent commercial pipelines and a good understanding of the market to plan for the procurement process.\n\n-   [Transitional and saving arrangements](/procurement-act-2023-guidance-transitional-and-savings-arrangements)\n    \n    11 July 2024 Guidance\n    \n-   [Contracting authorities](/procurement-act-2023-guidance-contracting-authorities)\n    \n    11 July 2024 Guidance\n    \n-   [Covered procurement](/procurement-act-2023-guidance-covered-procurement)\n    \n    11 July 2024 Guidance\n    \n-   [Exempted contracts](/procurement-act-2023-guidance-exempted-contracts)\n    \n    21 February 2025 Guidance\n    \n-   [Devolved contracting authorities](/procurement-act-2023-guidance-contracting-authority-definition)\n    \n    19 May 2025 Guidance\n    \n-   [Covered procurement objectives](/procurement-act-2023-guidance-covered-procurement-objectives)\n    \n    19 May 2025 Guidance\n    \n-   [Wales Procurement Policy Statement](/wales-procurement-policy-statement)\n    \n    22 August 2022 Policy and strategy\n    \n-   [Utilities contracts](/procurement-act-2023-guidance-utilities-contracts)\n    \n    15 January 2025 Guidance\n    \n-   [Concession contracts](/procurement-act-2023-guidance-concession-contracts)\n    \n    19 August 2024 Guidance\n    \n-   [Light touch contracts](/procurement-act-2023-guidance-light-touch-contracts)\n    \n    30 September 2024 Guidance\n    \n-   [Reserving contracts for supported employment providers](/procurement-act-2023-guidance-reserving-contracts-for-supported-employment-providers)\n    \n    5 September 2024 Guidance\n    \n-   [Pipeline notice](/procurement-act-2023-guidance-pipeline-notice)\n    \n    4 December 2024 Guidance\n    \n\n## Define\n\nAchieving flexible, efficient procurement process. This will encourage broad participation in processes that are open and accessible to all.\n\n-   [Valuation of contracts](/procurement-act-2023-guidance-valuation-contracts)\n    \n    19 August 2024 Guidance\n    \n-   [Thresholds](/procurement-act-2023-guidance-thresholds)\n    \n    1 January 2026 Guidance\n    \n-   [Below-threshold contracts](/procurement-act-2023-guidance-below-threshold-contracts)\n    \n    18 March 2025 Guidance\n    \n-   [Mixed procurement](/procurement-act-2023-guidance-mixed-procurement)\n    \n    16 December 2024 Guidance\n    \n-   [Planned procurement notice](/procurement-act-2023-guidance-planned-procurement-notice)\n    \n    4 December 2024 Guidance\n    \n-   [Preliminary market engagement](/procurement-act-2023-guidance-preliminary-market-engagement)\n    \n    4 December 2024 Guidance\n    \n-   [Technical specifications](/procurement-act-2023-guidance-technical-specifications)\n    \n    25 July 2024 Guidance\n    \n-   [Treaty state suppliers](/procurement-act-2023-guidance-treaty-state-suppliers)\n    \n    5 September 2024 Guidance\n    \n-   [Competitive tendering procedures and tender notices](/procurement-act-2023-guidance-competitive-tendering-procedures-and-tender-notices)\n    \n    28 March 2025 Guidance\n    \n-   [Direct award](/procurement-act-2023-guidance-direct-award)\n    \n    10 March 2025 Guidance\n    \n-   [Dynamic markets](/procurement-act-2023-guidance-dynamic-markets)\n    \n    11 March 2025 Guidance\n    \n-   [Frameworks](/procurement-act-2023-guidance-frameworks)\n    \n    21 February 2025 Guidance\n    \n-   [Lots](/procurement-act-2023-guidance-lots)\n    \n    9 September 2024 Guidance\n    \n-   [Conflicts of interest](/procurement-act-2023-guidance-conflicts-of-interest)\n    \n    9 September 2024 Guidance\n    \n\n## Procure\n\nEvaluating bidder compliance with exclusion grounds. Selecting suitable suppliers for the contract.\n\n-   [Time periods](/procurement-act-2023-guidance-time-periods)\n    \n    25 July 2024 Guidance\n    \n-   [Conditions of participation](/procurement-act-2023-guidance-conditions-of-participation)\n    \n    30 September 2024 Guidance\n    \n-   [Guidance: exclusions](/procurement-act-2023-guidance-exclusions)\n    \n    28 May 2025 Guidance\n    \n-   [Debarment](/procurement-act-2023-guidance-debarment)\n    \n    28 May 2025 Guidance\n    \n-   [Assessing competitive tenders](/procurement-act-2023-guidance-assessing-competitive-tenders)\n    \n    28 October 2024 Guidance\n    \n-   [Electronic communications](/procurement-act-2023-guidance-electronic-communications)\n    \n    30 September 2024 Guidance\n    \n-   [Modifying a competitive procurement](/procurement-act-2023-guidance-modifying-a-competitive-procurement)\n    \n    25 July 2024 Guidance\n    \n-   [Procurement termination notices](/procurement-act-2023-guidance-procurement-termination-notices)\n    \n    4 December 2024 Guidance\n    \n-   [Key performance indicators](/procurement-act-2023-guidance-key-performance-indicators)\n    \n    16 December 2024 Guidance\n    \n-   [Assessment summaries](/procurement-act-2023-guidance-assessment-summaries)\n    \n    30 September 2024 Guidance\n    \n-   [Contract award notices and standstill](/procurement-act-2023-guidance-contract-award-notices-and-standstill)\n    \n    18 February 2025 Guidance\n    \n-   [Contract details notices](/procurement-act-2023-guidance-contract-details-notices)\n    \n    11 March 2025 Guidance\n    \n-   [Procurement oversight (WPRU)](/procurement-act-2023-guidance-oversight)\n    \n    20 February 2025 Guidance\n    \n-   [Guidance: remedies](/procurement-act-2023-guidance-remedies)\n    \n    27 February 2025 Guidance\n    \n\n## Manage\n\nWorking with suppliers and managing the contract. Ensuring successful achievement of the contractual outcomes.\n\n-   [Electronic invoicing and payment](/procurement-act-2023-guidance-electronic-invoicing-and-payment)\n    \n    15 August 2025 Guidance\n    \n-   [Payments compliance notices](/procurement-act-2023-guidance-payments-compliance-notices)\n    \n    14 May 2025 Guidance\n    \n-   [Contract performance notices](/procurement-act-2023-guidance-contract-performance-notices)\n    \n    23 April 2025 Guidance\n    \n-   [Contract modifications](/procurement-act-2023-guidance-contract-modifications)\n    \n    31 March 2025 Guidance\n    \n-   [Contract terminations](/procurement-act-2023-guidance-contract-terminations)\n    \n    29 January 2025 Guidance\n    \n\n### Outside Gov.Wales\n\n-   [Procurement Act 2023](https://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2023/54/enacted#section-45-4)\n    \n    on legislation.gov.uk\n    \n-   [The Procurement (Wales) Regulations 2024](https://www.legislation.gov.uk/wsi/2024/782/contents/made)\n    \n    on legislation.gov.uk\n    \n\n## First published\n\n12 August 2024\n\n## Last updated\n\n15 August 2025\n\n## Part of\n\n-   [Public sector procurement (Sub-topic)](/public-sector-procurement)\n\n[Report anything wrong with this page](mailto:digital@gov.wales?url=https%3A//www.gov.wales/procurement-act-2023-guidance-documents&subject=Report%20on%20/procurement-act-2023-guidance-documents&body=Page%20URL%3A%20https%3A//www.gov.wales/procurement-act-2023-guidance-documents%0APage%20Title%3A%20Procurement%20Act%202023%3A%20guidance%20documents%0AYour%20report%3A%0A)\n\n## Share this page\n\n-   [Share this page via X](https://x.com/intent/tweet?url=https%3A//www.gov.wales/procurement-act-2023-guidance-documents)\n-   [Share this page via Facebook](https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=https%3A//www.gov.wales/procurement-act-2023-guidance-documents)\n-   [Share this page via Email](mailto:?body=https%3A//www.gov.wales/procurement-act-2023-guidance-documents&subject=Shared%20from%20gov.wales)\n\n[Back to top](#brig-top)\n\n-   [Contact us](/contact-us)\n-   [Accessibility](/accessibility-statement-govwales)\n-   [Copyright statement](/copyright-statement)\n-   [Cookies](/help/cookies)\n-   [Privacy](/website-privacy-policy)\n-   [Terms and conditions](/terms-and-conditions)\n-   [Modern slavery statement](/welsh-government-modern-slavery-statement)\n-   [Alternative languages](/alternative-languages)\n\n[Home](https://www.gov.wales/)",
