      "type": "answer",
      "text": "OK, plain English. Here's what actually goes in.\n\n## The Cover Page = one page, two halves\n\n**The first half is \"what are we doing.\" The second half is \"what happens if it goes wrong.\"** That's it. The rest (Standard Terms) stays the same for everyone and you don't touch it.\n\n### Half 1 — \"what are we doing\" (the SOW or business details)\n\n| Field | Plain English meaning | Example for Sharon's visa pack |\n|---|---|---|\n| **SOW number** | Just a label so you can find this contract later | \"Project 001 — Branding & Voice-Over\" |\n| **Provider** | Who's doing the work | Sharon Kostini |\n| **Customer** | Who's paying | AFJ Cardiff Ltd |\n| **Services** | What she's actually doing, in human words | \"Branding Kit design + voice-over narration for AFJ Cardiff digital launch\" |\n| **Deliverables** | What she hands over | \"Final logo, brand guidelines, voice-over files in MP3 + WAV\" |\n| **Who owns it** | Tick one: you own it now, or you own it when paid | \"Customer owns deliverables upon payment of fees\" |\n| **Third-party stuff?** | Tick: are you using fonts/photos/anything you didn't make? | Yes — she'll use Adobe Stock for one image |\n| **Fees** | How much, in plain money | £860 cash + 2% equity (12-month vesting) |\n| **Travel & expenses** | Will you bill for train tickets? | \"Yes, pre-approved in writing only\" |\n| **Payment Period** | How many days to pay after invoice | \"14 days\" |\n| **Invoice Period** | How often she sends invoices | \"Once, at end of project\" |\n| **Start date** | When work begins | Date you sign |\n| **End date** | When work ends | \"3 months from start date\" |\n| **Customer Obligations** | What YOU have to do so she can work | \"Provide brand brief, attend 2 review meetings\" |\n| **Any changes to Standard Terms** | Empty unless you need to add something | Usually blank |\n\n### Half 2 — \"what if it goes wrong\" (the Key Terms)\n\n| Field | Plain English meaning | Example |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Effective Date** | When the contract starts | Date of last signature |\n| **Governing Law** | Which country's rules apply | \"The laws of England and Wales\" |\n| **Chosen Courts** | Where you'd sue each other if it goes wrong | \"The courts of England and Wales\" |\n| **Covered Claims (each side)** | What each side promises to defend the other against | \"Provider covers: she didn't copy anyone's logo. Customer covers: stuff they gave her to use wasn't stolen.\" |\n| **General Cap Amount** | How much money either side can be sued for, normally | \"1× the fees paid in the last 12 months\" (= £860 cap for Sharon) |\n| **Increased Cap** | Higher cap for the really bad stuff (privacy, IP theft) | \"2× fees\" (£1,720) |\n| **Unlimited Claims** | Things with no cap at all (fraud, deliberate wrong-doing) | Usually blank |\n| **Insurance Minimums** | What insurance each side must have | \"Sharon must have £1m public liability\" |\n| **DPA** | Data Processing Agreement — attach if handling personal data | Usually attached separately |\n| **Security Policy** | What security standards you keep | \"ISO 27001\" or just blank for small jobs |\n| **Publicity Rights** | Can you put their logo on your website? | \"Yes, both ways\" or \"No, keep it quiet\" |\n| **Other Changes** | Anything else to override the standard terms | Usually blank unless you want to add something |\n\nThen you sign: Provider's printed name, title, email, date; Customer's same.\n\n---\n\n## What about the **other** agreements — what changes?\n\nThe shape is identical. Only the fields change. Quick rundown:\n\n### Mutual NDA (the simple one — for Sharon's pre-work / partner chats)\n- **Purpose** — \"why are we sharing secrets?\" (e.g., \"Evaluating whether to enter into a working relationship\")\n- **Effective Date** — date of last signature\n- **MNDA Term** — how long you can share secrets (1 year is standard)\n- **Term of Confidentiality** — how long the secrets stay secret after sharing (2 years is standard)\n- **Governing Law** — England and Wales\n- **Jurisdiction** — courts of England and Wales\n- **Optional changes** — usually nothing\n\nThat's it. One page. Done in 10 minutes.\n\n### Independent Contractor Agreement (for Mariam / Hope / one-off advisors)\n- **Same shape as PSA**, but the \"Provider\" is the freelancer, \"Customer\" is you. Most fields identical. You'd add: who owns the work (you do, once paid), how many revisions (e.g., 2 rounds), what's a \"deliverable\" vs a \"draft.\"\n\n### Cloud Service Agreement (for if you sell any software later)\n- This one's heavier — adds a Subscription Period (e.g., monthly/annual), auto-renewal terms, uptime commitment, AI training opt-in/opt-out, EU Data Act clause.\n\n### Partnership Agreement (for A&B Cymru / Stiwdio / school partners)\n- Adds: how you refer business to each other, logo rights, exclusivity (or not), how to terminate gracefully.\n\n### Terms of Service (for your portal's users)\n- Adds: who can use it, what they can't do, your liability limit, how you handle abuse.\n\n---\n\n## My recommendation for you specifically\n\nFor each of your ventures, write a one-page \"Cover Page Cheat Sheet\" like this:\n\n**Sharon (Scrollytelling Wales) — PSA**\n- Provider: Sharon Kostini · Customer: Andrea Kwabena Technologies Ltd · Services: Branding + voice-over · Fees: £860 cash + 2% equity (vest 12m) · End: 3 months · Governing Law: England & Wales · Cap: 1× fees (£860) · Insurance: £1m PL · Sign with Dropbox Sign.\n\n**Plamedi (AFJ Cardiff) — Founders Service Agreement + IP Assignment addendum**\n- Two docs: one is an FSA (Founders Service Agreement), the other is an IP Assignment (\"everything you create belongs to AFJ Cardiff Ltd\"). Both on Common Paper templates. Sign in your capacity as Director of AFJ Cardiff Ltd.\n\n**Alaya (FirstGens) — Independent Contractor + Sweat Equity addendum**\n- ICA covering your role as fractional CTO (15% equity, 1-year cliff, 4-year vesting). IP Assignment so FirstGens owns the ADRs you write.\n\n**Mariam (Black Flamingo) — short LOI + add-on equity share option**\n- Letter of Intent first (Common Paper), then if she does the equity scheme, use Vestd (cheaper than SeedLegals for EMI options).\n\n**Hope (charity) — Advisory Agreement**\n- Common Paper Independent Contractor Agreement, £0 cash fee, advisory role, no IP transfer (charity-specific exemption).\n\n---\n\nWant me to actually write the **Cover Page for Sharon's visa pack** first — fully filled in, ready for her signature? That's the highest-stakes one (Home Office review, financial implications, personal relationship). If you can see one fully completed example, the other four are easy copies of the same pattern.",
      "timestamp": 1782216331203
    },
    {
      "type": "thought",
      "text": "Good, now I have the actual Cover Page structure for both the NDA and the PSA. Let me explain what goes in a Cover Page in plain English, using these two as concrete examples. The user asked for plain English, so I need to be really clear and avoid legal jargon.\n\nThe Cover Page has two halves:\n1. **SOW / business half** — what you're actually doing, what you're being paid, when\n2. **Key Terms / legal half** — governing law, liability caps, who pays for what insurance\n\nLet me write this as a practical guide with concrete \"fill in the blank\" examples using the user's actual ventures (Alaya/FirstGens, Plamedi/AFJ, Sharon/ScrollytellingWales).",
