      "text": "The user wants to focus on Plamedi now and forget Sharon. They want a fully filled-in Cover Page for the Plamedi / AFJ Cardiff engagement. Let me build this properly.\n\nBased on the pastes I've read, here's what I know about Plamedi and AFJ Cardiff:\n\n- Plamedi runs AFJ Cardiff — an AfroJam / Afro-dance organisation\n- She's currently transitioning from sole trader to Ltd (AFJ Cardiff Ltd)\n- She's based in Cardiff/Newport, Wales\n- Andie (the user) is her \"Digital Officer\" / \"Platform Architect\" / \"Fractional CTO\"\n- They want a **Founders Service Agreement (FSA)** or **Consultancy Agreement** + **IP Assignment**\n- Equity considerations: none mentioned for Andie from Plamedi (this is different from Alaya/Sharon)\n- The April 3 paste describes:\n  - \"Incorporate AFJ Ltd\" \n  - \"Founders Service Agreement\" via SeedLegals\n  - \"Consultancy Agreement + SLA Appendix\"\n  - \"IP Waiver & Assignment\"\n  - \"Equity Option Letter\" for board members\n  - Director appointment\n  - PI insurance £1m cover for Andie (named as protected person)\n- Stiwdio Newport = physical membership / institutional passport\n- Azure / OCI free tier for hosting\n- GoRules decision engine\n- n8n automation\n- Cloudflare tunnel\n\nSo the documents needed for Plamedi are:\n1. **Consultancy Agreement + SLA** (with Andie as the consultant, AFJ Cardiff Ltd as the customer) — using Common Paper PSA template\n2. **IP Assignment** (addendum to the PSA, or as a separate agreement)\n3. **Mutual NDA** (between Andrea Kwabena Technologies Ltd and AFJ Cardiff Ltd)\n4. **DPA** (if any personal data is processed)\n\nLet me draft these properly, fully filled in, with Common Paper-style formatting. I'll use plain English and the actual structure of Common Paper documents. The user asked for it \"in plain English\" — so I should make sure each field's value is comprehensible.\n\nLet me build all three documents as ready-to-execute cover pages.\n\nStructure of my response:\n1. Quick context: what set of documents she needs\n2. Document 1: Mutual NDA Cover Page (Andrea Kwabena Technologies Ltd ↔ AFJ Cardiff Ltd)\n3. Document 2: Consultancy Agreement + SLA Cover Page (Andie as Provider, AFJ Cardiff Ltd as Customer)\n4. Document 3: IP Assignment (as an \"Other Changes\" addendum to the PSA, or as standalone)\n5. Implementation notes: signing, sequencing, what to keep\n\nLet me make sure to use the user's actual name. The user is \"Andie\" / Andrea Enning / Andrea Kwabena (sounds like the user goes by Andie, and has both \"Enning\" and \"Kwabena\" as surnames — possibly Italian birth name and Ghanaian heritage, \"Andrea Kwabena Technologies\" was mentioned as a Welsh sole-proprietor).\n\nLooking back at the pastes:\n- \"Andrea Enning\" — Italian given name + surname (from CV files: \"Andrea Enning Updated CV\")\n- \"Andrea Kwabena Technologies\" — Ghanaian name + UK Ltd mentioned in the Alaya/FirstGens paste\n- \"Andie Enning\" — what WhatsApp messages show\n\nSo the user's full name seems to be Andrea \"Andie\" Enning, with Ghanaian connection (Kwabena). The Ltd is \"Andrea Kwabena Technologies Ltd\" — but I should let the user confirm. For now I'll use \"Andrea Kwabena Technologies Ltd\" as the entity name, since that's what the pastes use, and \"Andie Enning\" as the person.\n\nFor Plamedi's Ltd, the pastes mention \"AFJ Cardiff Ltd\" as the corporate entity, while her current state is sole trader under her UTR.\n\nNow let me draft.\n\nAlso — given the context, the Consultancy Agreement covers:\n- Andie's role as Digital Officer / Fractional CTO\n- Equity (if any) — the pastes don't mention Plamedi giving Andie equity, but they do mention \"IP Assignment\" which means work product belongs to AFJ\n- Compensation — likely deferred (no salary now, given she's just incorporated; or a small fee)\n- Term — open-ended or 12 months\n- SLA — uptime target, response time, etc.\n- Insurance — Andie needs £1m PI; this should be reflected\n\nLet me build this